details.overview: They were the bad boys of hockey — a team bought by a man with mob ties, run by his 17-year-old son, and with a rep for being as violent as they were good.
The first 11 semi-finalists perform for a chance to win $1 million and be named the most talented act in America.
As Pat considers whether he should come clean to Courtney about Eclipso's past, a surprise visit from Crock and Paula catches him and Barbara off guard.

Kelly meets Joey, a young orphaned alien boy, who is acting out in foster care because he fears there is something wrong with his brother Orlando, who is incarcerated. Kelly asks Kara to help her investigate and they stumble upon abuse at the prison. Meanwhile, Nyxly crashes one of Nia's dreams and asks her for help.

Survivors become separated when they are engulfed by a gigantic dust cloud after the fall of the south tower. We follow them as they wrestle with the trauma of their experiences and desperately search for missing loved ones. When the dust settles after the collapse of the north tower, we witness emotional reunions and heart-breaking losses.

details.bottomTitle: S01E05 - I'm Coming for You, Brother
details.overview: First responders look at the vast pile of debris at ground zero and wonder how anyone could still be alive. But one group of firefighters who were inside the north tower as it collapsed managed to survive miraculously. Now they are trapped, and as they radio “mayday” for help, other firefighters must race against time to locate and rescue their “brothers” in a dangerous and unstable ocean of rubble.
As the wagon train attempts to cross the Blue Mountains, Ezekiel worries their journey has been cursed by God. Benny tries to make amends with Trig.
Zoe’s birthday celebration reopens old wounds, even as the group begins to grow closer.

details.bottomTitle: S01E04 - What If… Doctor Strange Lost His Heart Instead of His Hands?
details.overview: A grief-stricken Doctor Strange uses the Eye of Agamotto in a dangerous effort to change the past.
Dug comes face to face with his sworn enemy.
Dug learns that puppies are cute, but also a lot of work!
Dug smells something he has never smelled before.
Dug finds out he doesn't love fireworks as much as Carl does.
Russell helps Dug find a new way to communicate with his "neighbors."

details.bottomTitle: S05E14 - Chapter Ninety: The Night Gallery
details.overview: Cheryl enlists the help of Archie, Kevin, Fangs and Reggie after she learns there is palladium underneath her maple groves. Betty and Alice confront a trucker who may have been involved in Polly's disappearance. Jughead and Archie each confront events from their past.
Only 5 acts from the previous show move on to the finals, one of which is voted through during the show.

Terry's nose growth has prevented him from meeting his grandkids; Remi has alligator-like skin and is not used to taking care of herself; Austin has an embarrassing birthmark right next to his eyelid; Mary Jo has a throbbing bump on her neck.

The couples return to Houston to live together for the first time as husband and wife, but settling into day-to-day life is a rough transition for anyone. Now our stranger spouses are challenged with the struggles of everyday life and the decision to fight for their marriages--or flee from them.

In the aftermath of the towers collapsing, two former Marines and an ex-paramedic head to ground zero to search for survivors. Together they stumble upon two Port Authority police officers trapped 50-feet beneath the rubble. Putting their own lives on the line and against all odds, the volunteers manage to pull off one of the most daring and inspiring rescue stories of the day.
Callie and Gael struggle to make time for each other. Mariana tries to redeem herself with the Fight Club Girls. Malika realizes there are other ways to help people facing incarceration injustices.
Harry's newfound talent brings an unexpected visitor to town. Alma decides to take matters into her own hands.
Crane enlists the help of lethal assassin Lady Vic, who has a troubled history with Dick and Barbara. Meanwhile, Kory and Gar bring Blackfire back to Wayne Manor.
The U.S.S. Cerritos is dispatched to a planet to investigate an unexplained sighting of a dangerous Mugato.

A tornado puts the school on lockdown and Helen believes it's coming specifically for her; the kids pass the time by writing fan fiction, "shipping" various combinations of faculty members; Mary, Stef and Michelle devise a plan to escape the school.
Jack has the students form a fake cult to sabotage Principal Durbin's new school uniforms; Mary, Stef and Michelle prepare to see one of their favorite artists who is in town to perform.

Jack attempts to get closer with the guys at work by inviting them over for a game night; Helen helps Principal Durbin grow a backbone; Stef and Mary try to coax information out of Michelle about the court case she was a juror on.

When the A.P. Bio students reunite Jack with his deadbeat dad, Jack plots revenge by trying to expose his allegedly reformed father; a witch foretells of a grim future for Mary, Stef and Michelle that divides the women.

details.bottomTitle: S04E05 - The Perfect Date From Hell
details.overview: When Jack discovers his new girlfriend's therapy homework requires dating him, he turns the tables on her; Principal Durbin goes undercover to determine which faculty member is most worthy of a very special prize.

details.bottomTitle: S04E06 - Love, for Lack of a Better Term
details.overview: Victor attempts to catch up to his peers and become a man by sending Ashlanda a risqué photo; Grace and Anthony try to "Parent Trap" Mary and Principal Durbin after overhearing a conversation that makes them take pity on the single adults.
When Jack's girlfriend says she's going to dinner with a male friend, a jealous Jack tags along; Principal Durbin, Mary, Stef and Michelle take Helen out to cheer her up after a breakup.

Jack is enraged to find that the A.P. Bio students have stolen his beloved Harvard pen after he asked them not to touch it; Principal Durbin and Helen repeatedly fail the superintendent's inspections.

details.bottomTitle: S04E09 - You Beat Me to the Punch
details.overview: At a luau party with the crew, Zoey accepts Luca’s career advice, making Aaron uncomfortable. Doug and Kiela navigate a roadblock in their relationship, while Vivek tries to help Nomi and Ana take their minds off the LSATs.

details.bottomTitle: S04E08 - The Pleasing Voice of the Masters
details.overview: Talon and Luna fight against the gods but not all goes as planned. Janzo is reunited with someone from his past. Meanwhile, Garret and Janzo feud over the fate of a prisoner. Lastly, Tobin fights to save Talon.

details.topTitle: What We Do in the Shadows
details.overview: A forbidden artifact is used to help Nandor court a health club employee.
An old enemy comes face-to-face with Baba. Jerlamarel struggles to accept a life without sight.
With things turning around for Richmond, it’s time for everyone to work on their issues—like Ted’s discomfort, Nate’s confidence, and Roy’s attention.
Apologizing is tough, and in this era of public mea culpas, forgiveness isn't guaranteed. What makes for a good apology, and why does it hold such power?
Kanan and Marvin's side hustle goes awry. Raq seeks revenge for the attack on Scrappy. Jukebox suffers a devastating blow.
Kristen, David, and Ben are sent to Cornell University, at the request of Bishop Marx, to investigate an electrode-based experiment.

Axe dispatches Wags to dig up dirt on Prince, discovering a weakness that could wreck Prince’s ambitions. A visit to Axe Cap puts Wendy and Tanner at odds. Chuck looks for alternative methods to save his father, but a college-aged mistake threatens to sidetrack him.
Maggie's team gets hunted by Reapers. Carol, Rosita, Magna, and Kelly set off to catch horses.
Local law enforcement turn up the heat on the Codys, as further secrets threaten to destabilize the family. Deran gets some news about Adrian. Craig discovers Renn has been keeping a secret.

Ellie has surprising news to tell her friends; Ari's ex-husband makes a big impression; Steven quits his job while Alina prepares for her move; Kenny and Armando finally start planning their wedding; Jenny has only one option left to stay in India.
Rick gets new sidekicks, while Morty makes a new friend.
Rick is living his best anime life, making new friends and taking down new enemies.
Liz's plan does not go as expected, putting herself, Isobel and Michael in danger. Eduardo confides in Alex.

Jaclyn has a lump on the back of her head that causes her emotional distress. Shane has a growth between his eyes that could put him in danger at his electrician job. Brittany has seen multiple doctors about the sores on her body with no answers.
Stan gets in over his head trying to impress Toshi's dad. Klaus and Jeff head to the country for a weekend getaway.

The last 11 semi-finalists perform for a chance to win $1 million and be named the most talented act in America.
As Pat and Courtney clash over their next steps in their search for Eclipso, ominous weather conditions in Blue Valley hint that he may be near.

Supergirl intervenes when a building in the Heights that was set aside for low income housing is suddenly at risk to be sold to a major corporation. Supergirl recruits Orlando to help her win over the city, but things go awry when Nyxly shows up. Meanwhile, Nia trains with her mother.
Ezekiel, Benny, and the farmers face starvation as they try to survive a blizzard. Todd gets into politics.
A new beginning is soured when a single decision turns Bobby’s life on its head.
The Gargoyles get as hard as stone; Solid Snake must master the walk of shame; The Avengers learn to curb their enthusiasm.

Bobby goes all in on music while the rest of the Clan struggles with life in the projects.
The Clan becomes disillusioned with their paths as Bobby prepares to steer them in a new direction.
When The Avengers are infected by a zombie plague, surviving heroes search for a cure.
Just as the passengers settle into the rhythms of life in the bunker, a sudden food shortage forces them to consider making another risky journey.
With the generator shut down, temperatures and tempers soar, sparking a tense standoff. The Colonel finds a damning piece of evidence at the air base.
After a distressing chain of events, Thea and Mathieu lead a search for a new plane, and the officers plot their revenge on Sylvie.
At the bunker, the trial soon gives way to more twisted schemes. The group searching for seeds encounters a disoriented stranger.
As Thea and team attempt to lure Gia out of the vault, Ines searches for a way back into the bunker, and Rik confides in the ambassador.
The crisis aboard the plane threatens to leave the travelers stranded. Fearing for their lives, Sylvie and the others hatch a plan to flee the bunker.

But it's not until she reunites with her former bandmates Valerie and Melody, that she opens up about the real reason why she's back. Veronica gets creative after a surprise visit from her old friend Alexandra Cabot. Toni steps in to help Tabitha and Veronica land a deal.
Only 5 acts from the previous show move on to the finals, one of which is voted through during the show.

Callie questions her choices. Mariana interviews for a new job. Malika considers an offer away from DPN. Gael is forced to put his priorities into perspective, and Alice must make a tough decision.
The dark history of Provincetown and its residents are brought to light.
"Robot Chicken" asks if Totoro is overweight and doesn't like the answer; Jigsaw outgrows his tricycle; The Washington Generals destroy the entire world of basketball.

Gotham’s crime families meet to discuss the fear toxin’s hold on the city - only to be confronted by the mastermind himself. As Dick and Barbara consult the Oracle to preempt Crane’s next move, Starfire and Blackfire reach an understanding.
Mariner and Boimler try to track down the location of a legendary Starfleet party while the bridge crew deals with an insecure alien diplomat.
Talon and Zed see ominous visions beneath the Outpost. Garret tests his relationship with Talon. Janzo solves the riddle of an old relic.

details.topTitle: What We Do in the Shadows
details.overview: An old flame returns and an ancient vehicle is resurrected.
Edo’s leadership is called into question. Baba and Haniwa meet a secret tribe of warriors known as The Compass.
Ted and Dr. Sharon realize they might have to meet each other halfway. Tensions are high as the team prepares for the semifinal.

details.overview: The Robot Chicken writers think Disney is running out of classics to remake; Luke Skywalker is a little too comfy inside that Taunaun; Midsommars' big problem was it wasn't cute enough.

Desperate to be helpful, Lucifer assists an exasperated Carol investigate a drag queen's death. Ella and Chloe look into Carol’s mysterious background.
Loony Lucifer and cartoon Chloe find themselves trapped in an animated loop. Amenadiel prepares for his new job. Dan returns to the city of angels.

details.overview: Lucifer reconnects with a few former flames in hopes of disproving Rory's claim. Dan tries to find someone— anyone—who can actually see him.

details.bottomTitle: S06E05 - The Murder of Lucifer Morningstar
details.overview: Not believing that he could have abandoned his future daughter, Lucifer sets out to prove an alternate theory: He must have been murdered.

details.bottomTitle: S06E06 - A Lot Dirtier Than That
details.overview: Wanting to do well on his first day with the LAPD, Amenadiel crosses paths with a racist detective from his past. Lucifer tries to bond with Rory.
Just as Eve and Maze's wedding day arrives, Eve's ex, Adam—yes, that Adam—shows up hoping to reconcile. Ella delivers some distressing news.

details.bottomTitle: S06E08 - Save the Devil, Save the World
details.overview: Lucifer says he's finally ready to be God, but his non-functioning wings would tend to disagree. Linda reluctantly shares the first draft of her book.
Lucifer tries to enjoy what may be his last day on Earth. Dan's killer escapes from prison. Chloe drops a serious bombshell.
Desperate to rescue Rory, Lucifer and Chloe confront her kidnapper with guns and wings blazing. Lucifer finally comes to terms with his purpose.
As the planet warms, hurricanes could become even more dangerous and destructive. What can be done to survive and minimize the threat of these storms?
HEA's Andrei makes shocking accusations against Elizabeth's sister-in-law.
Kanan struggles with a harsh truth after word gets back to Raq that he's behind the bad crack on the streets.
Bishop Marx tasks the team to investigate a UFO sighting, spotted by an air force pilot.

As Prince spirals in the wake of a scandal, Axe looks to take his attack to the next level, putting Taylor's business in the crossfire; Chuck reckons with his father's mortality; Wendy worries the money may be getting to Tanner.
Daryl and Dog get captured by the Reapers and reconnect with a familiar figure from their past.
Desperate for cash, and with pressure mounting, the Codys discover what they thought was a solution to their problems may be the biggest threat of them all.

Ellie heads to Colombia without a plan; Jenny hopes to get answers with the Hare Krishnas; Kenny has been keeping a secret; Bini confronts Ari's ex-husband; Evelin drops a bomb on her sisters; Alina decides to test Steven's faithfulness.

On the eve of the worst crisis in human history, Congresswoman Jennifer Brown clashes with the President. Her children Yorick and Hero reach an emotional crossroads. None of them know their lives are about to change forever.

details.bottomTitle: S01E02 - Would the World Be Kind
details.overview: After a mass casualty event wipes out every creature with a Y chromosome, President Jennifer Brown responds to the crisis. Yorick fears he may be the only survivor. Hero attempts to right a wrong.

With Jennifer and Yorick reunited, Agent 355 pitches a plan for what comes next. The dead President's daughter, Kimberly, circles Jennifer's secret. Meanwhile, Nora Brady and her daughter Mack say goodbye to home.
Liz needs Rosa's help. Maria learns what Jones wants from her. Michael and Alex team up to help save Max.
President Biden rolls out a major vaccination mandate, Roy Wood Jr. worries about the rise of the Mu COVID-19 variant, and Dr. Anthony Fauci talks vaccine disinformation.

details.overview: "Robot Chicken" shows how "Batman Beyond's" training goes way beyond Batman's training; a deleted scene makes "Cats" a masterpiece; B... Pudding is determined to bring it on.
The top 10 acts perform one last time for their chance to win $1 million and be named the most talented act in America.
Cindy and her new team make their move against the JSA leading to an epic showdown.

Supergirl and team must stop Nyxly from vanquishing a familiar face from Supergirl's past - Mr. Mxyzptlk. Mxy returns and explains Nyxly's dark history to the super team in the best way he knows how - in song form. Meanwhile, Lena visits her mother's birthplace in Ireland, eager to dig into her past but is shocked by the small town's icy reception towards her.
The wagon train faces its final showdown.
Nicki Minaj makes an anti-vaccination appeal, Dulcé Sloan investigates a sperm recession in the U.S., and Gabrielle Union discusses “You Got Anything Stronger?,” her new book of essays.
RZA makes a risky move to squash old beef.

details.bottomTitle: S11E07 - May Cause Random Wolf Attacks
details.overview: "Robot Chicken" locks and loads for a Darkwing Duck hunt; the show's greatest warriors assemble for a battle beyond the stars; even Cobra Commander can't resist the Tiger King.
Pressure on Masha intensifies, as she juggles the competing needs of her guests, discord amongst her staff and her absolute commitment to healing the Marconi family.

details.bottomTitle: S01E06 - What If… Killmonger Rescued Tony Stark?
details.overview: An American soldier called Killmonger rescues Tony Stark when his Humvee is attacked in Afghanistan.

details.bottomTitle: S04E06 - The Ultimate Showdown in Fake Universe! Clash of Blue and Scarlet

details.overview: After hearing some unexpected news about his former commanding officer, Archie opens up to Uncle Frank about his time in the Army. Veronica comes up with a clever way to raise funds after Chad calls the SEC on her. Cheryl and Kevin attempt to take control of the ministry. Jughead goes on an apology tour.
Host Terry Crews reveals whom America has chosen as the winner. Also featuring special guest performers and not-to-be missed surprises.
As our five pairs of married strangers enter their third week of marriage, one couple contemplates using the "L word" while the other four do anything they can to ignite a fire between them.

Bats have been implicated in deadly epidemics such as COVID-19 and Ebola, yet scientists are discovering evidence that they may hold a key to a longer and healthier life. From caves in Thailand and Texas to labs around the globe, NOVA meets the scientists who are decoding the superpowers of the bat.
Harry struggles to keep Alma under control. Doris is pushed past her limits.
Trevor highlights civilian deaths in Afghanistan, Desi Lydic examines the mis-treatment of women during childbirth, and Carmelo Anthony discusses “Where Tomorrows Aren’t Promised.”

details.bottomTitle: S11E08 - May Cause Lucid Murder Dreams
details.overview: Naruto has trained and "Robot Chicken" writers think he's ready for the test; The Force evolves into something new and deadly; "Robot Chicken" teaches Martin Scorcese a few things about filmmaking.

details.bottomTitle: S02E01 - I Hate the Game of Keys
details.overview: A few months have passed since the last game. Adriana left Oscar and now he lives with Gaby... and Mica. Valentin came out of the closet and is trying to be happy in this new stage of his life. Barbara and Leo were stripped of their belongings by Aurelia's lawsuit but they adopted Carmen and now have a “throuple.” Everyone seems to be in crisis, unable to make sense of their lives.

Adriana blames Siena for everything that has happened since they met. Siena introduces her to Astrid, and they both convince her this is her chance to live with total freedom. Gloria, Barbara´s mother, appears uninvited at the footstep of Barbara´s house. Valentín tries to come out of the closet to his mother, while Gaby and Oscar try to rekindle their former spark.

details.bottomTitle: S02E03 - Takes a New Game to Forget An Old Game
details.overview: Adriana attends her first game with Siena and Astrid. Thanks to Guillermo, a super-hot teacher and Siena, she is initiated into sex between more than two people. Valentin cannot convince his mom to let him tell his father the truth. Barbara can´t stand her mother being in her house and Gaby notices that Oscar has no interest in what is about to happen to them as a couple.

After winning the stripping contest, Leo is convinced that his true calling is to be a dancer. Valentin tries to come out to his father, but his mother interrupts by telling her husband that Gaby is pregnant with her son´s child. Astrid prepares a game of keys in her house to help Siena "get over" Adriana. However, nothing will go as planned.

When a white, woke, twenty-something ally to social justice causes discovers video evidence of a disputed police incident in the background of his highly embarrassing sex tape, a savvy young lawyer and her mentor strategize on how to best use the tape and witness to save an innocent man from prison.

After losing his daughter to gun violence, a grieving father pursues a new job as a PR director at the National Gun Lobby, where he’s befriended by a coworker who starts to suspect the man’s motives may be far more dangerous than they seem.
As an emboldened Crane looks to filter his poison through Gotham’s water system, Starfire - still plagued by visions - enlists Blackfire and Superboy’s help, and Gar finally tracks down Jason.
Anomaly consolidation day on the U.S.S. Cerritos leaves the Lower Deckers with mixed emotions. Captain Freeman attempts to negotiate peace on the Pakled home world.
Talon and Luna return to a familiar tomb. Janzo and Wren find themselves in a precarious position. Meanwhile, Zed, Munt and Nedra must play a deadly game against the gods.

Kofun and Toad arrive in Pennsa just as Maghra makes a life-changing decision. Baba, Paris and Haniwa run into a trusted friend.
Controversy and betrayal strike TMS as a new year approaches. Alex faces a difficult decision.

"Robot Chicken" writers had fun in health class; the "Kingdom Hearts" gang have another use for their keys; the "Robot Chicken" nerd has a monstrous housewives nightmare.
The Instagram face. A shapely posterior. Cosmetic surgery can make the latest beauty trends a reality. Explore its origins and effects, inside and out.
Moordale's friskiest come together again — in more ways than one. Otis sports a 'stache but hides a secret. Jean comes clean. A head teacher arrives.
Makeovers take over when Ruby gives Otis a magnetic revamp and Hope tones the school down. Way down. Elsewhere, Eric and Adam look to level up.
Self-expression is out as uniforms sweep the student body. Aimee opens up about the assault while Jackson bonds with cool nonbinary student Cal.
In the cold light of day, can sex turn into intimacy, and vice versa? Ruby recoils from Otis. Maeve connects with Isaac. Abstinence roils Moordale.

Home is where the heat is. Jean contends with a hot mess and a cold shoulder. Maeve deals with a mum on the run. The "sex school" finally goes public.
As a new day dawns, Moordale's fate hangs in the balance. Aimee spills. Eric confesses. Otis haunts the hospital. Honesty matters now, more than ever.
Hoping to win easy money, a broke and desperate Gi-hun agrees to take part in an enigmatic game. Not long into the first round, unforeseen horrors unfold.
Split on whether to continue or quit, the group holds a vote. But their realities in the outside world may prove to be just as unforgiving as the game.

details.bottomTitle: S01E03 - The Man with the Umbrella
details.overview: A few players enter the next round — which promises equal doses of sweet and deadly — with hidden advantages. Meanwhile, Jun-ho sneaks his way inside.

Ahead of the last round, distrust and disgust run deep among the finalists. Jun-ho makes a getaway, determined to expose the game's dirty secrets.
The final round presents another cruel test — but this time, how it ends depends on just one player. The game's creator steps out of the shadows.

Ben, David, and Kristen investigate the RSM Fertility clinic - since so many of their past cases have led back to the ominous clinic.

Alexandrians encounter Hilltop squatters; Eugene’s group undergoes orientation at the Commonwealth.
J and Pope take a road trip to clean up the aftermath of some family business that went sideways. Deran and Craig scout a new mark with the help of Frankie.

Corey faces the wrath of Evelin's sisters; Alina and Steven's reunion is less than ideal; Ellie gets an unexpected call; Armando is on a mission to tell his family big news; Ari learns Bini's sisters still don't trust her.
On Jennifer's orders, Yorick and Agent 355 search for a geneticist who can unravel the mystery of how he survived. Meanwhile, Hero and Sam encounter a dangerous group of women.
Liz and Max continue to search for a way to stop Jones. Michel is worried about Alex and elsewhere, Isobel finds a big piece of the puzzle.

When Dave starts researching his genealogy, he makes a surprising discovery: he and Calvin are more than just neighbors. Also, Tina offers to help Gemma when she’s overcome with morning sickness, and inadvertently stumbles on a new business idea.
Nurses experience pandemic burnout in the U.S., Trevor rolls out the second annual Pandemmy Awards, and Olympic gymnast Aly Raisman discusses her documentary special “Darkness to Light.”

Knowing that she can make a difference, Kelly embraces her power and fully steps into her role as Guardian. Joined by Supergirl, Alex, Diggle and team, Guardian leads the way to restoring justice to the fallen community.

Tension is thick as the Clan works together to build a home recording studio.

To show just how pervasive Winchester's race problems are, Lionel sets out to write a feature on Troy and makes some unexpected discoveries.
Coco jumps at the chance to join Troy at a party for wealthy donors, but the evening leaves her questioning his priorities.
With tensions running high before the town hall, Sam tries to patch up her relationship, Coco steals Troy's thunder, and Lionel makes a bold move.

details.overview: Thor, who never learned to be a good hero, throws an out-of-control intergalactic party on Earth.

details.bottomTitle: S05E17 - Chapter Ninety-Three: Dance of Death
